00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:01:37,120 --> 00:01:40,720
[EP7: The Mysterious Chapter 23]

2
00:01:47,040 --> 00:01:48,813
What was that?

3
00:01:49,520 --> 00:01:51,646
<i>An ambulance.</i>

4
00:01:52,719 --> 00:01:54,880
Why is there an ambulance?

5
00:01:54,880 --> 00:01:57,313
<i>I'm at the hospital.</i>

6
00:01:58,719 --> 00:02:00,840
Lawyer Xu, what happened?

7
00:02:00,840 --> 00:02:02,623
<i>My stomach's just acting up.</i>

8
00:02:02,623 --> 00:02:04,422
<i>Nothing serious.</i>

9
00:02:06,680 --> 00:02:08,240
Well, get some rest.

10
00:02:08,240 --> 00:02:10,440
Hope you feel better soon.

11
00:02:15,570 --> 00:02:19,848
[Emergency Center]

12
00:02:19,848 --> 00:02:22,240
What are you two doing here?

13
00:02:22,240 --> 00:02:24,376
You're looking a lot better now.

14
00:02:24,376 --> 00:02:25,480
Does it still hurt?

15
00:02:25,480 --> 00:02:26,610
Not anymore.

16
00:02:26,610 --> 00:02:28,040
It doesn't? Then have something to drink.

17
00:02:29,138 --> 00:02:30,280
Okay.

18
00:02:30,280 --> 00:02:31,400
I'm not that hungry.

19
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:34,133
You need to eat something,
even if you're not hungry.

20
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:39,160
Ambulance siren samples?

21
00:02:39,160 --> 00:02:41,104
Lawyer Xu, what are you listening to that for?

22
00:02:41,104 --> 00:02:43,993
No reason. Just changing up
my musical taste recently.

23
00:02:46,320 --> 00:02:48,560
That's a new one.

24
00:02:48,560 --> 00:02:51,360
First time I've ever heard of someone
"changing their music taste"

25
00:02:51,360 --> 00:02:53,320
to ambulance sirens.

26
00:02:53,320 --> 00:02:54,880
All right.

27
00:02:54,880 --> 00:02:56,400
Life getting a little too dull for you?

28
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:58,400
Looking for some excitement?

29
00:02:58,400 --> 00:03:01,681
Mr. Xu, a Miss Ruan is here to see you.

30
00:03:01,681 --> 00:03:03,620
Let her in. Thanks.

31
00:03:04,716 --> 00:03:06,320
How did Ruan Yu find out?

32
00:03:06,320 --> 00:03:09,504
Xu Huai Song. You old fox.

33
00:03:09,504 --> 00:03:12,080
I thought you were listening to sirens
to get your thrills.

34
00:03:12,080 --> 00:03:14,640
Turns out you're trying to find a girlfriend.

35
00:03:14,640 --> 00:03:15,840
Take these.

36
00:03:15,840 --> 00:03:18,235
Go ahead and eat.

37
00:03:18,235 --> 00:03:19,720
I'm taking them, then.

38
00:03:19,720 --> 00:03:21,520
Okay.

39
00:03:40,560 --> 00:03:42,919
How was I supposed
to know you didn't eat lunch?

40
00:03:42,919 --> 00:03:45,080
You never told me.

41
00:03:45,080 --> 00:03:46,599
What do you mean, I never told you?

42
00:03:46,599 --> 00:03:48,159
I sent you a message on WeChat.

43
00:03:48,159 --> 00:03:51,580
You must have sent it to the wrong person.
I never got it.

44
00:03:56,028 --> 00:03:58,836
[Bring me some porridge for lunch.
New District Hospital, Room 106.]

45
00:04:06,038 --> 00:04:08,780
<i>Bring me some porridge for lunch.</i>

46
00:04:14,360 --> 00:04:17,146
<i>New District Hospital, Room 106.</i>

47
00:04:22,680 --> 00:04:24,723
<i>So the message wasn't for me.</i>

48
00:04:24,723 --> 00:04:28,280
<i>Should I go in now or not?</i>

49
00:04:28,960 --> 00:04:31,541
I want that porridge right now.

50
00:04:32,360 --> 00:04:35,720
Fine! I'll go buy it for you now.

51
00:04:37,080 --> 00:04:38,537
Miss Ruan?

52
00:04:38,537 --> 00:04:40,000
Lawyer Liu,

53
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:41,560
you're buying porridge?

54
00:04:41,560 --> 00:04:42,680
How'd you know?

55
00:04:42,680 --> 00:04:44,980
Come in, come in.

56
00:04:46,060 --> 00:04:47,290
Miss Ruan,

57
00:04:47,290 --> 00:04:48,480
what are you doing here?

58
00:04:48,480 --> 00:04:49,720
Lawyer Xu,

59
00:04:49,720 --> 00:04:51,760
your porridge.

60
00:04:55,640 --> 00:04:57,480
I sent that to Liu Mao.
How did it end up with you?

61
00:04:57,480 --> 00:05:00,379
- Sorry to have bothered you.
- It's no problem.

62
00:05:04,560 --> 00:05:06,800
Lawyer Xu, I didn't know you were sick.

63
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:07,920
If I had,

64
00:05:07,920 --> 00:05:10,560
I really wouldn't have kept you up
so late talking about the case yesterday.

65
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:12,720
Don't worry about it.

66
00:05:12,720 --> 00:05:15,960
<i>When you were talking about the case,
he wasn't checked in yet.</i>

67
00:05:15,960 --> 00:05:17,519
<i>On the way to the hospital,</i>

68
00:05:17,519 --> 00:05:20,000
<i>he was staring at his phone's signal,</i>

69
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:21,759
<i>so scared the call would drop,</i>

70
00:05:21,759 --> 00:05:23,160
<i>but he didn't dare turn on his mic,</i>

71
00:05:23,160 --> 00:05:25,360
<i>afraid he'd wake you up.</i>

72
00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:29,393
<i>Love really does make a fool of us all.</i>

73
00:05:30,920 --> 00:05:32,079
Lawyer Xu,

74
00:05:32,079 --> 00:05:33,560
are you feeling any better today?

75
00:05:33,560 --> 00:05:35,400
No.

76
00:05:35,400 --> 00:05:37,879
Lawyer Xu, you really need to start

77
00:05:37,879 --> 00:05:40,446
taking better care of your stomach.

78
00:05:40,446 --> 00:05:41,600
You know,

79
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:43,360
the stomach is an emotional organ.

80
00:05:43,360 --> 00:05:44,970
When you're in a good mood,

81
00:05:44,970 --> 00:05:46,889
your stomach feels good.

82
00:05:46,889 --> 00:05:47,973
Miss Ruan,

83
00:05:47,973 --> 00:05:49,140
you're a writer,

84
00:05:49,140 --> 00:05:50,559
so you must have a way with words.

85
00:05:50,559 --> 00:05:53,353
When you have a moment,
you should chat more with Lawyer Xu.

86
00:05:53,353 --> 00:05:54,959
It'll put him in a good mood,

87
00:05:54,959 --> 00:05:56,648
which will be a great help

88
00:05:56,648 --> 00:05:59,193
in his recovery.

89
00:05:59,193 --> 00:06:01,028
It's just the same old problem.
Don't put her on the spot.

90
00:06:01,028 --> 00:06:03,273
How is this putting her on the spot?

91
00:06:03,273 --> 00:06:04,406
It's not a problem at all.

92
00:06:04,406 --> 00:06:05,720
I'm here anyway,

93
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:08,744
and I don't have anything else to do today.

94
00:06:08,744 --> 00:06:10,829
See what she said?

95
00:06:10,829 --> 00:06:13,330
So considerate.

96
00:06:14,082 --> 00:06:16,262
Thank you.

97
00:06:18,337 --> 00:06:20,171
What kind of way is that to eat?

98
00:06:20,171 --> 00:06:22,173
It's a Su City specialty.

99
00:06:22,173 --> 00:06:25,079
It's how we locals eat.

100
00:06:25,079 --> 00:06:27,178
How would you know that?

101
00:06:27,178 --> 00:06:29,772
I'm also from Su City.

102
00:06:30,933 --> 00:06:32,832
I did my research.

103
00:06:37,356 --> 00:06:39,856
It's in your WeChat profile.

104
00:06:44,253 --> 00:06:45,447
Miss Ruan,

105
00:06:45,447 --> 00:06:47,874
you're here to see Lawyer Xu too?

106
00:06:48,639 --> 00:06:50,399
Lawyer Xu, didn't you just say you weren't--

107
00:06:50,399 --> 00:06:52,913
He's hungry now.

108
00:06:52,913 --> 00:06:54,748
We're done talking.

109
00:06:54,748 --> 00:06:56,240
We should get going.

110
00:06:56,240 --> 00:06:57,720
There's still work at the firm.

111
00:06:57,720 --> 00:06:59,545
Bye.

112
00:06:59,545 --> 00:07:02,240
By the way, Lawyer Xu, that email
you sent me at three in the morning...

113
00:07:02,240 --> 00:07:05,660
I just saw it.
I'll send you the file right away.

114
00:07:06,885 --> 00:07:08,160
<i>Three in the morning?</i>

115
00:07:08,160 --> 00:07:10,040
<i>Didn't Xu Huai Song say he fell asleep too,</i>

116
00:07:10,040 --> 00:07:13,183
<i>so he didn't hang up the call?</i>

117
00:07:13,183 --> 00:07:15,143
Are you saying I was sleepwalking

118
00:07:15,143 --> 00:07:17,123
at three in the morning?

119
00:07:19,839 --> 00:07:23,026
He means...

120
00:07:23,026 --> 00:07:25,640
you must have been dreaming.

121
00:07:26,404 --> 00:07:28,039
I sent it to you, right?

122
00:07:28,039 --> 00:07:29,319
- I sent it to him.
- Really?

123
00:07:29,319 --> 00:07:30,800
I sent it to him.

124
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:32,600
Let's go.

125
00:07:33,495 --> 00:07:35,559
- We're leaving.
- Are you serious?

126
00:07:36,319 --> 00:07:37,800
Sit.

127
00:07:40,127 --> 00:07:43,386
No, wait, Bro Mao, it was definitely Lawyer Xu
who sent that email.

128
00:07:44,360 --> 00:07:45,674
You've been with me for so many years.

129
00:07:45,674 --> 00:07:47,885
How can you be so clueless?

130
00:07:47,885 --> 00:07:50,066
Think about it again.

131
00:08:01,160 --> 00:08:02,607
Come to think of it,

132
00:08:02,607 --> 00:08:05,317
Lawyer Xu acts strangely
whenever Miss Ruan is around.

133
00:08:05,317 --> 00:08:06,778
Like the day he got back,

134
00:08:06,778 --> 00:08:10,115
he made me put on a whole act,
saying Ms. Zhang was in trouble.

135
00:08:10,115 --> 00:08:12,079
Later, when I called
to ask when to pick him up,

136
00:08:12,079 --> 00:08:14,780
he randomly told me he hadn't eaten.

137
00:08:16,413 --> 00:08:19,073
That sly old fox.

138
00:08:31,439 --> 00:08:33,263
Lawyer Xu, are you finished eating?

139
00:08:33,263 --> 00:08:35,182
Yes, all done.

140
00:08:35,182 --> 00:08:36,200
Okay.

141
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:38,185
- Thank you.
- It was nothing.

142
00:08:38,185 --> 00:08:39,436
Well, get some rest.

143
00:08:39,436 --> 00:08:40,895
I'll be heading back now.

144
00:08:40,895 --> 00:08:44,149
That counter-plagiarism file, I organized it
and brought it over for you.

145
00:08:44,149 --> 00:08:45,817
You can take a look
when you have a free moment.

146
00:08:45,817 --> 00:08:48,462
Okay. Could you please hand it to me?

147
00:08:48,462 --> 00:08:49,926
Yes.

148
00:08:52,241 --> 00:08:54,340
- Here.
- Okay, thanks.

149
00:09:03,585 --> 00:09:05,628
<i>Ruan Yu's fried rice cakes
even come with after-sales service.</i>

150
00:09:05,628 --> 00:09:07,881
<i>She seems pretty into you.</i>

151
00:09:07,881 --> 00:09:10,008
<i>Why not test the waters?</i>

152
00:09:10,008 --> 00:09:12,226
<i>You might have a shot.</i>

153
00:09:27,150 --> 00:09:29,236
Lawyer Xu, I'll be going now.

154
00:09:29,236 --> 00:09:30,440
Okay.

155
00:09:30,440 --> 00:09:32,979
You rest up.

156
00:09:33,657 --> 00:09:35,457
Wait.

157
00:09:36,618 --> 00:09:38,273
Your manuscript...

158
00:09:38,273 --> 00:09:41,840
it seems to be missing a chapter.

159
00:09:41,840 --> 00:09:43,873
Chapter 23.

160
00:10:07,039 --> 00:10:09,979
<i>Xu Huai Song.</i>

161
00:10:24,519 --> 00:10:26,380
<i>Ruan Yu.</i>

162
00:10:27,002 --> 00:10:30,302
<i>Do you want me...</i>

163
00:10:38,847 --> 00:10:40,437
Do you want me

164
00:10:40,437 --> 00:10:41,975
to read it?

165
00:10:41,975 --> 00:10:43,775
No!

166
00:10:45,395 --> 00:10:46,897
Why not?

167
00:10:46,897 --> 00:10:49,650
Chapter 23 is a transitional chapter.

168
00:10:49,650 --> 00:10:51,818
It should be pretty important, right?

169
00:10:51,818 --> 00:10:53,000
It's...

170
00:10:53,654 --> 00:10:54,970
It's not that important.

171
00:10:54,970 --> 00:10:56,279
Whether it's important or not

172
00:10:56,279 --> 00:10:58,900
is for me to decide after I've read it.

173
00:10:59,701 --> 00:11:01,159
Now?

174
00:11:01,159 --> 00:11:02,799
Now.

175
00:11:02,799 --> 00:11:04,640
Please, have a seat.

176
00:11:14,299 --> 00:11:17,727
Lawyer Xu,
I don't have the original manuscript with me.

177
00:11:18,480 --> 00:11:21,639
It should be on the website's back end, right?

178
00:11:21,639 --> 00:11:23,360
<i>He's a lawyer.</i>

179
00:11:23,360 --> 00:11:24,720
<i>How does he know his way around</i>

180
00:11:24,720 --> 00:11:27,540
<i>the back end of a women's fiction site?</i>

181
00:11:40,588 --> 00:11:41,701
Lawyer Xu,

182
00:11:41,701 --> 00:11:43,578
the signal in this room isn't very good.

183
00:11:43,578 --> 00:11:45,705
I'll send it to you after I get back.

184
00:11:45,705 --> 00:11:48,160
The hospital has Wi-Fi.

185
00:11:48,160 --> 00:11:50,900
The password is four sixes, four eights.

186
00:12:06,601 --> 00:12:08,269
I've already sent it to you.

187
00:12:08,269 --> 00:12:10,647
Well, I'll be going now.

188
00:12:17,029 --> 00:12:19,900
Lawyer Xu, what's wrong?

189
00:12:21,992 --> 00:12:24,243
Is your stomach bothering you again?
I'll go get a doctor.

190
00:12:24,243 --> 00:12:26,713
It's okay, it's okay.

191
00:12:28,158 --> 00:12:30,750
I've been straining my eyes too much lately.

192
00:12:30,750 --> 00:12:32,080
My eyes hurt.

193
00:12:32,080 --> 00:12:35,146
<i>I thought he was here for a stomach ache.</i>

194
00:12:37,075 --> 00:12:38,509
Since my eyes are bothering me,

195
00:12:38,509 --> 00:12:41,268
you can read it to me. Thank you.

196
00:12:42,675 --> 00:12:44,138
What did you say?

197
00:12:44,138 --> 00:12:47,120
I still roughly remember the plot
involving the Poet.

198
00:12:47,120 --> 00:12:49,440
You just need to read it to me once.
Once we confirm there are no issues,

199
00:12:49,440 --> 00:12:52,189
we can close the book on this.

200
00:12:52,189 --> 00:12:53,940
<i>You'll have no issues,</i>

201
00:12:53,940 --> 00:12:56,513
<i>but I'll have a huge one.</i>

202
00:12:57,611 --> 00:12:59,195
Lawyer Xu, that's not necessary.

203
00:12:59,195 --> 00:13:02,031
I've already confirmed there are
no problems with that chapter.

204
00:13:02,031 --> 00:13:03,700
The most dangerous place

205
00:13:03,700 --> 00:13:05,560
is the safest place.

206
00:13:05,560 --> 00:13:07,245
And the reverse is also true.

207
00:13:07,245 --> 00:13:09,414
The more certain you are there's no problem,

208
00:13:09,414 --> 00:13:12,133
the more likely it is that there is one.

209
00:13:13,543 --> 00:13:14,866
<i>It's fine, it's fine.</i>

210
00:13:14,866 --> 00:13:16,295
<i>It's just a dream the main character has.</i>

211
00:13:16,295 --> 00:13:18,039
<i>What's it got to do with me?</i>

212
00:13:18,039 --> 00:13:19,360
<i>It's just reading a dream sequence</i>

213
00:13:19,360 --> 00:13:21,639
<i>that goes a little something like this...</i>

214
00:13:21,639 --> 00:13:24,579
<i>Life is short.
It'll be over before you know it.</i>

215
00:13:50,413 --> 00:13:52,730
Chapter 23.

216
00:13:52,730 --> 00:13:54,279
He Shi Qian.

217
00:13:54,279 --> 00:13:56,962
- He...
- Forget it.

218
00:13:56,962 --> 00:13:59,622
I'll just read it myself later.

219
00:14:00,382 --> 00:14:01,946
Okay.

220
00:14:03,559 --> 00:14:05,660
I'm leaving, Lawyer Xu.

221
00:14:08,807 --> 00:14:10,607
Goodbye.

222
00:14:29,411 --> 00:14:30,578
<i>Song,</i>

223
00:14:30,578 --> 00:14:32,117
<i>what room are you in?</i>

224
00:14:32,117 --> 00:14:34,859
<i>Mom and I will come see you in a bit.</i>

225
00:14:38,840 --> 00:14:40,996
We're here, Mom.

226
00:14:40,996 --> 00:14:42,632
Stop eating so much candy.

227
00:14:42,632 --> 00:14:44,159
You're too old for that.

228
00:14:44,159 --> 00:14:46,699
And you have to use floss.

229
00:14:51,513 --> 00:14:53,519
You made me come with you to the dentist.

230
00:14:53,519 --> 00:14:55,919
Where are we?

231
00:14:55,919 --> 00:14:57,960
Mom, since you're already here,

232
00:14:57,960 --> 00:14:59,240
just go in and see my brother.

233
00:14:59,240 --> 00:15:00,775
He's sick.

234
00:15:00,775 --> 00:15:03,069
This is when he needs family support the most.

235
00:15:03,069 --> 00:15:04,324
I told you a long time ago,

236
00:15:04,324 --> 00:15:05,905
I don't have a son.

237
00:15:05,905 --> 00:15:07,600
He is not my family.

238
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:09,600
Look at you.

239
00:15:09,600 --> 00:15:12,320
Don't be angry. Don't say that.

240
00:15:12,320 --> 00:15:14,759
If you want to go, go by yourself.

241
00:15:14,759 --> 00:15:16,559
Liar.

242
00:15:16,559 --> 00:15:18,560
Mom.

243
00:15:28,178 --> 00:15:29,946
Song.

244
00:15:32,766 --> 00:15:34,130
Let me see you.

245
00:15:34,130 --> 00:15:36,937
What happened?

246
00:15:36,937 --> 00:15:38,312
Let me see.

247
00:15:38,312 --> 00:15:40,773
Why are you so pale?

248
00:15:40,773 --> 00:15:42,700
You look like you're on death's door.

249
00:15:42,700 --> 00:15:45,780
If you're going to be so dramatic,
you can just not talk.

250
00:15:48,399 --> 00:15:50,620
Why are you alone?

251
00:15:51,952 --> 00:15:54,872
Mom is actually really worried about you,

252
00:15:54,872 --> 00:15:57,039
but she's been so busy with work
these past two days

253
00:15:57,039 --> 00:15:58,639
she didn't have time to come.

254
00:15:58,639 --> 00:16:03,179
So she sent me as her special envoy
to check on you.

255
00:16:05,966 --> 00:16:07,425
Lawyer Xu,

256
00:16:07,425 --> 00:16:08,953
I forgot something.

257
00:16:09,636 --> 00:16:11,759
Come in.

258
00:16:11,759 --> 00:16:13,200
Who's this pretty girl?

259
00:16:13,200 --> 00:16:14,519
Not worried about your brother's life,

260
00:16:14,519 --> 00:16:17,311
but you're interested in the pretty girls?

261
00:16:17,311 --> 00:16:18,519
- I'm sorry.
- Thank you.

262
00:16:18,519 --> 00:16:19,960
I'll be going now.

263
00:16:19,960 --> 00:16:21,519
Sis.

264
00:16:21,519 --> 00:16:23,357
Hello.

265
00:16:23,357 --> 00:16:26,194
I'm the sister of this very difficult,
handsome man.

266
00:16:26,194 --> 00:16:27,862
My name is Xu Huai Shi.

267
00:16:27,862 --> 00:16:31,305
Hello. I'm Lawyer Xu's...

268
00:16:32,242 --> 00:16:33,326
client.

269
00:16:33,326 --> 00:16:34,986
Client?

270
00:16:35,578 --> 00:16:37,413
Let me guess.

271
00:16:37,413 --> 00:16:39,200
You wouldn't happen to be

272
00:16:39,200 --> 00:16:41,660
Ruan Yu, would you?

273
00:16:44,046 --> 00:16:46,480
How did you know?

274
00:16:46,480 --> 00:16:49,480
I heard my brother mention you.

275
00:16:49,480 --> 00:16:51,510
He said he's currently handling a case

276
00:16:51,510 --> 00:16:53,554
for a writer named Ruan Yu.

277
00:16:53,554 --> 00:16:56,346
And you just have this aura of a well-read,

278
00:16:56,346 --> 00:16:57,759
articulate, cultured person.

279
00:16:57,759 --> 00:17:00,240
I just guessed and got it right.

280
00:17:00,240 --> 00:17:01,919
I can't believe Lawyer Xu has

281
00:17:01,919 --> 00:17:04,380
a sister as charming as you.

282
00:17:04,982 --> 00:17:06,817
Song, you should reflect on

283
00:17:06,817 --> 00:17:09,620
why she said "I can't believe."

284
00:17:10,696 --> 00:17:12,162
I didn't mean it like that.

285
00:17:12,162 --> 00:17:13,324
Well.

286
00:17:13,324 --> 00:17:14,720
It's okay, Ruan Yu.

287
00:17:14,720 --> 00:17:17,940
My brother's social skills well, you get it.

288
00:17:18,720 --> 00:17:20,748
If Lawyer Xu were half as charming as you,

289
00:17:20,748 --> 00:17:23,960
he could probably double his caseload.

290
00:17:23,960 --> 00:17:26,357
A lawyer's caseload depends
on their ability to handle cases,

291
00:17:26,357 --> 00:17:28,549
not on being a smooth talker.

292
00:17:28,549 --> 00:17:30,800
Whether he's charming or not,

293
00:17:30,800 --> 00:17:32,983
or if he could take on more cases,
I really don't know.

294
00:17:32,983 --> 00:17:36,459
But at least he wouldn't still be single.

295
00:17:38,684 --> 00:17:41,852
<i>Doesn't he have a girlfriend?</i>

296
00:17:41,852 --> 00:17:43,160
I'm telling you,

297
00:17:43,160 --> 00:17:44,897
even if pigs learned to fly,

298
00:17:44,897 --> 00:17:46,790
he probably still wouldn't find a girlfriend.

299
00:17:46,790 --> 00:17:48,720
He's been single for 28 years.

300
00:17:48,720 --> 00:17:50,039
Xu Huai Shi, let me remind you,

301
00:17:50,039 --> 00:17:52,440
spreading someone's private information
may constitute an infringement of a citizen's

302
00:17:52,440 --> 00:17:55,158
personal information and a crime of defamation.

303
00:17:55,158 --> 00:17:58,046
How is this "spreading"?

304
00:17:58,046 --> 00:18:00,119
If I told a lot of people,
that would be spreading.

305
00:18:00,119 --> 00:18:02,915
I only told Ruan Yu.

306
00:18:02,915 --> 00:18:06,720
And she won't tell anyone else, right?

307
00:18:06,720 --> 00:18:08,379
Of course not.

308
00:18:08,379 --> 00:18:10,131
I will definitely keep

309
00:18:10,131 --> 00:18:11,425
Lawyer Xu's secret.

310
00:18:11,425 --> 00:18:12,700
Yes.

311
00:18:18,056 --> 00:18:20,808
Shouldn't you hurry up
and wash some fruit for her

312
00:18:20,808 --> 00:18:22,523
as hush money?

313
00:18:22,523 --> 00:18:24,473
Okay.

314
00:18:24,473 --> 00:18:26,440
No need,
I'm just grabbing my things and leaving.

315
00:18:26,440 --> 00:18:28,240
- You're leaving already?
- It's no trouble, no trouble at all.

316
00:18:28,240 --> 00:18:31,236
I was going to eat some anyway.

317
00:18:31,236 --> 00:18:33,696
How about this, I'll go wash it.

318
00:18:33,696 --> 00:18:35,799
I need to wash this container anyway.

319
00:18:35,799 --> 00:18:37,074
You're too kind.

320
00:18:37,074 --> 00:18:38,240
- It's nothing.
- I'll go with you.

321
00:18:38,240 --> 00:18:39,573
No.

322
00:18:42,331 --> 00:18:44,131
Close the door.

323
00:18:48,336 --> 00:18:50,846
What?

324
00:18:51,715 --> 00:18:53,842
When we go back out there,

325
00:18:53,842 --> 00:18:56,302
don't say anything stupid.

326
00:18:56,302 --> 00:19:00,139
Song, I'm totally trying
to be your wingman here.

327
00:19:00,139 --> 00:19:02,016
Think about it. In just a few sentences,

328
00:19:02,016 --> 00:19:03,806
I established your "single guy" persona.

329
00:19:03,806 --> 00:19:06,680
What if Ruan Yu mistakenly
thought you had a girlfriend?

330
00:19:06,680 --> 00:19:09,599
Even if she was interested,
she wouldn't dare make a move.

331
00:19:09,599 --> 00:19:11,901
Kids should stay out of adults' business.

332
00:19:11,901 --> 00:19:14,278
If I don't get involved, how long
are you going to drag this out?

333
00:19:14,278 --> 00:19:15,988
Mr. Great Lawyer,

334
00:19:15,988 --> 00:19:18,783
why are you and Ruan Yu still stuck in

335
00:19:18,783 --> 00:19:21,026
a client-lawyer relationship?
Have you ever thought about that?

336
00:19:21,026 --> 00:19:22,580
Of course, I know.

337
00:19:23,205 --> 00:19:24,720
It's because...

338
00:19:24,720 --> 00:19:26,759
she doesn't know I recognized her.

339
00:19:26,759 --> 00:19:28,119
Wrong.

340
00:19:28,119 --> 00:19:29,418
It's because you and Ruan Yu

341
00:19:29,418 --> 00:19:31,504
haven't seen each other in so many years.

342
00:19:31,504 --> 00:19:34,079
You're not sure if she still likes you.

343
00:19:34,079 --> 00:19:35,174
Or rather,

344
00:19:35,174 --> 00:19:37,009
if she could like the real you.

345
00:19:37,009 --> 00:19:39,129
You're not confident,
so you don't dare make a reckless move,

346
00:19:39,129 --> 00:19:41,931
worried you'll scare her away.

347
00:19:41,931 --> 00:19:43,015
Let me put it this way:

348
00:19:43,015 --> 00:19:45,726
You may understand how to win a lawsuit,
but that doesn't mean you understand love.

349
00:19:45,726 --> 00:19:47,960
You may understand love,
but that doesn't mean you understand women.

350
00:19:47,960 --> 00:19:50,240
You may understand women,
but that doesn't mean you understand

351
00:19:50,240 --> 00:19:52,400
that sin^2(x) + cos^2(x) = 1.

352
00:19:52,400 --> 00:19:54,799
Now you're just being ridiculous.

353
00:19:54,799 --> 00:19:56,559
You're a high school student
who hasn't even graduated,

354
00:19:56,559 --> 00:19:58,680
and you're here teaching me,
a man almost 30, how to date.

355
00:19:58,680 --> 00:20:00,599
You think that makes sense?

356
00:20:00,599 --> 00:20:02,039
You can underestimate your opponent,

357
00:20:02,039 --> 00:20:04,960
but you should never underestimate
a member of Gen Z.

358
00:20:04,960 --> 00:20:08,458
I'm done talking to you.
I'm going to go bond with Ruan Yu.

359
00:20:08,458 --> 00:20:11,080
Don't say anything stupid.

360
00:20:12,296 --> 00:20:14,435
Ruan Yu, I'll help you.

361
00:20:14,435 --> 00:20:15,839
No need, I've got it.

362
00:20:15,839 --> 00:20:17,634
Don't be polite.

363
00:20:17,634 --> 00:20:20,094
I'll prep this, then.

364
00:20:25,440 --> 00:20:26,440
Ruan Yu,

365
00:20:26,440 --> 00:20:28,200
my brother specifically told me

366
00:20:28,200 --> 00:20:30,146
to come out here, work more, and talk less,

367
00:20:30,146 --> 00:20:32,130
so I wouldn't bother you with my chattering.

368
00:20:32,130 --> 00:20:34,316
He's pretty thoughtful, isn't he?

369
00:20:34,316 --> 00:20:37,153
Your brother is more than thoughtful.

370
00:20:37,153 --> 00:20:38,250
Actually,

371
00:20:38,250 --> 00:20:40,657
I quite enjoy talking with you.

372
00:20:40,657 --> 00:20:44,379
So, do you prefer talking to me,
or to my brother?

373
00:20:46,519 --> 00:20:47,663
It's different.

374
00:20:47,663 --> 00:20:49,790
Talking to you is fun.

375
00:20:49,790 --> 00:20:53,360
Talking to your brother is reassuring.

376
00:20:53,360 --> 00:20:56,255
When he talks to me about the case,
he's very professional.

377
00:20:56,255 --> 00:20:57,799
And besides professional?

378
00:20:57,799 --> 00:21:00,579
Do you have any other opinions of him?

379
00:21:01,469 --> 00:21:02,793
An opinion?

380
00:21:03,559 --> 00:21:06,319
Well, when you writers are working,

381
00:21:06,319 --> 00:21:08,400
you like to create a persona
for a character, right?

382
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:11,579
Like, what kind of person is he?

383
00:21:14,160 --> 00:21:16,901
If he were in a novel,

384
00:21:16,901 --> 00:21:18,839
he would probably be

385
00:21:18,839 --> 00:21:22,120
the aloof, untouchable "cool city guy" type.

386
00:21:22,908 --> 00:21:24,232
<i>Good news.</i>

387
00:21:24,232 --> 00:21:26,940
<i>My brother's "cool guy" persona is intact.</i>

388
00:21:28,539 --> 00:21:29,788
Ruan Yu,

389
00:21:29,788 --> 00:21:32,640
you're so pretty, a lot of guys must like you.

390
00:21:32,640 --> 00:21:34,940
Do you have a boyfriend?

391
00:21:38,119 --> 00:21:39,839
Not yet.

392
00:21:39,839 --> 00:21:42,319
So what type of guy

393
00:21:42,319 --> 00:21:44,406
do you like?

394
00:21:46,079 --> 00:21:48,992
I like guys who are as charming as you.

395
00:21:48,992 --> 00:21:50,359
<i>Oh no.</i>

396
00:21:50,359 --> 00:21:51,720
<i>The persona is too strong.</i>

397
00:21:51,720 --> 00:21:53,854
<i>But even without the persona,</i>

398
00:21:53,854 --> 00:21:57,404
<i>my brother's mouth
is more venomous than charming.</i>

399
00:21:57,404 --> 00:22:00,780
<i>Does that mean he's out of the running?</i>

400
00:22:02,489 --> 00:22:05,079
Huai Shi, what part of the city
did you come from today?

401
00:22:05,079 --> 00:22:06,200
Su City.

402
00:22:06,200 --> 00:22:08,160
You go to high school in Su City?

403
00:22:08,160 --> 00:22:10,454
Yes, my brother and I both went

404
00:22:10,454 --> 00:22:12,924
to Su City No. 1 High School.

405
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:20,799
That case you hired my brother for,

406
00:22:20,799 --> 00:22:23,180
how's it progressing?

407
00:22:24,052 --> 00:22:25,163
We're almost there.

408
00:22:25,163 --> 00:22:27,000
The court date is soon.

409
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:28,960
Did you run into any difficulties?

410
00:22:28,960 --> 00:22:31,642
We're missing a piece of evidence
we had planned on.

411
00:22:31,642 --> 00:22:33,945
But it won't affect anything.

412
00:22:36,523 --> 00:22:38,640
<i>It was probably the evidence
I was supposed to provide</i>

413
00:22:38,640 --> 00:22:41,612
<i>about the sale of the outline.</i>

414
00:22:41,612 --> 00:22:43,404
<i>That whole thing was fake to begin with,</i>

415
00:22:43,404 --> 00:22:46,400
<i>and I couldn't fabricate
any transaction records.</i>

416
00:22:46,400 --> 00:22:49,686
<i>Besides, perjury is illegal.</i>

417
00:22:55,663 --> 00:22:56,750
Ruan Yu,

418
00:22:56,750 --> 00:22:57,880
don't worry.

419
00:22:57,880 --> 00:22:59,480
If you have any trouble, just ask my brother.

420
00:22:59,480 --> 00:23:01,419
He's really good.

421
00:23:05,920 --> 00:23:07,680
I'm back.

422
00:23:07,680 --> 00:23:09,888
Song, have an apple.

423
00:23:09,888 --> 00:23:11,181
I don't want one.

424
00:23:11,181 --> 00:23:13,017
Just give one to Ruan Yu.

425
00:23:13,017 --> 00:23:14,559
Here, you have it.

426
00:23:14,559 --> 00:23:15,799
Thank you.

427
00:23:15,799 --> 00:23:17,799
Can I get your WeChat?

428
00:23:17,799 --> 00:23:18,960
Xu Huai Shi.

429
00:23:18,960 --> 00:23:20,200
Sure.

430
00:23:20,200 --> 00:23:22,653
Let me scan you.

431
00:23:22,653 --> 00:23:24,111
Let's keep in touch.

432
00:23:24,111 --> 00:23:25,966
Okay.

433
00:23:27,407 --> 00:23:29,977
Lawyer Xu, I won't disturb you any longer.

434
00:23:29,977 --> 00:23:32,599
You get some rest.

435
00:23:32,599 --> 00:23:34,622
Thanks for the hush money.

436
00:23:34,622 --> 00:23:37,480
And thank you for the porridge.

437
00:23:37,480 --> 00:23:38,626
Okay, I'm leaving.

438
00:23:38,626 --> 00:23:40,550
- Bye.
- Bye.

439
00:23:40,550 --> 00:23:42,740
Take care.

440
00:23:44,720 --> 00:23:46,619
Xu Huai Shi.

441
00:23:51,639 --> 00:23:53,624
What did you say when you were out there?

442
00:23:53,624 --> 00:23:55,576
You don't like apples, do you?

443
00:23:57,855 --> 00:23:59,440
Not big ones,

444
00:23:59,440 --> 00:24:00,680
not small ones.

445
00:24:00,680 --> 00:24:02,566
Not red ones or green ones.

446
00:24:02,566 --> 00:24:03,953
You don't like any of them.

447
00:24:03,953 --> 00:24:06,759
Because what you like isn't apples at all.

448
00:24:06,759 --> 00:24:08,473
Speak English.

449
00:24:08,473 --> 00:24:09,640
You wouldn't understand.

450
00:24:09,640 --> 00:24:10,949
Song,

451
00:24:10,949 --> 00:24:12,993
you still have a lot to learn.

452
00:24:12,993 --> 00:24:14,620
It's okay, let's not rush.

453
00:24:14,620 --> 00:24:16,173
Let's take it slow.

454
00:24:16,173 --> 00:24:18,039
Well, I'm heading out. Bye.

455
00:24:18,039 --> 00:24:19,759
What red apple, green apple?

456
00:24:19,759 --> 00:24:21,659
Bye...

457
00:24:29,845 --> 00:24:32,420
What's wrong with red apples?

458
00:24:47,736 --> 00:24:49,914
[Doesn't have a girlfriend]

459
00:25:16,890 --> 00:25:20,746
[There's nothing you can't get over,
just that you can never go back.]

460
00:25:24,920 --> 00:25:26,279
<i>Wrong.</i>

461
00:25:26,279 --> 00:25:27,599
<i>It's because you and Ruan Yu</i>

462
00:25:27,599 --> 00:25:29,653
<i>haven't seen each other in so many years.</i>

463
00:25:29,653 --> 00:25:32,240
<i>You're not sure if she still likes you.</i>

464
00:25:32,240 --> 00:25:33,407
<i>Or rather,</i>

465
00:25:33,407 --> 00:25:35,264
<i>if she could like the real you.</i>

466
00:25:35,264 --> 00:25:37,286
<i>You're not confident,
so you don't dare make a reckless move,</i>

467
00:25:37,286 --> 00:25:40,506
<i>worried you'll scare her away.</i>

468
00:25:50,160 --> 00:25:52,333
<i>Song?</i>

469
00:25:52,333 --> 00:25:54,720
- It's me.
- You're out of the hospital?

470
00:25:54,720 --> 00:25:56,390
<i>I am.</i>

471
00:25:56,390 --> 00:25:59,440
<i>I have a question for you.</i>

472
00:25:59,440 --> 00:26:01,602
Earlier today at the hospital,

473
00:26:01,602 --> 00:26:04,920
you were talking about red apples,
green apples, and all that.

474
00:26:04,920 --> 00:26:06,650
What did you mean?

475
00:26:06,650 --> 00:26:09,568
Your reaction time is impressively slow.

476
00:26:09,568 --> 00:26:13,076
But, better late than never.

477
00:26:13,076 --> 00:26:15,039
Spare me the idioms.

478
00:26:15,039 --> 00:26:16,720
Just get to the point.

479
00:26:16,720 --> 00:26:18,400
I asked Ruan Yu today

480
00:26:18,400 --> 00:26:21,220
what type of guy she likes.

481
00:26:22,457 --> 00:26:24,559
And what did she say?

482
00:26:24,559 --> 00:26:26,920
She said...

483
00:26:26,920 --> 00:26:28,440
She said...

484
00:26:28,440 --> 00:26:30,560
I'm a little tired.

485
00:26:35,470 --> 00:26:37,784
She said she likes charming guys.

486
00:26:37,784 --> 00:26:41,226
She said she likes charming guys?

487
00:26:41,226 --> 00:26:43,687
But here's a friendly little tip.

488
00:26:43,687 --> 00:26:44,799
I don't think

489
00:26:44,799 --> 00:26:47,277
you can overdo the cool guy act.

490
00:26:47,277 --> 00:26:51,443
What Ruan Yu might like is...

491
00:26:51,443 --> 00:26:53,424
Is...

492
00:26:53,424 --> 00:26:55,200
Is...

493
00:26:55,200 --> 00:26:57,500
Is what?

494
00:26:59,559 --> 00:27:01,599
I'm thirsty.

495
00:27:01,599 --> 00:27:03,399
Okay.

496
00:27:04,000 --> 00:27:05,859
Please.

497
00:27:06,710 --> 00:27:08,377
Someone who's aloof but charming.

498
00:27:08,377 --> 00:27:10,714
Aloof but charming.

499
00:27:10,714 --> 00:27:12,466
Can a person be aloof

500
00:27:12,466 --> 00:27:15,266
and charming at the same time?

501
00:27:16,039 --> 00:27:19,540
That's a pretty tough standard to meet.

502
00:27:20,200 --> 00:27:21,598
But...

503
00:27:21,598 --> 00:27:24,260
I have an excellent role model
you can learn from.

504
00:27:24,260 --> 00:27:26,339
What role model?

505
00:27:29,022 --> 00:27:30,970
Welcome to Xu's Love Class.

506
00:27:30,970 --> 00:27:32,526
Satisfaction guaranteed, affordable price.

507
00:27:32,526 --> 00:27:35,788
One-on-one tutoring for only 666 yuan.

508
00:27:38,907 --> 00:27:40,409
[Tap to receive]

509
00:27:40,409 --> 00:27:43,073
Sent. What role model? Tell me.

510
00:27:43,073 --> 00:27:44,788
Do you remember I asked you

511
00:27:44,788 --> 00:27:46,930
for some allowance money a while back
to go to a concert?

512
00:27:46,930 --> 00:27:48,417
I remember. And?

513
00:27:48,417 --> 00:27:52,150
My Can's stage presence is just so versatile.

514
00:27:52,150 --> 00:27:54,799
When he's playing a ballad,

515
00:27:54,799 --> 00:27:56,680
he's both elegant and aloof.

516
00:27:56,680 --> 00:27:57,840
- A ballad.
- Right, a ballad.

517
00:27:57,840 --> 00:28:00,640
- Elegant. Aloof.
- Elegant, aloof.

518
00:28:00,640 --> 00:28:02,266
Like this.

519
00:28:02,266 --> 00:28:03,725
Like this?

520
00:28:03,725 --> 00:28:06,480
Like this.

521
00:28:06,480 --> 00:28:09,146
You're so bad at this.
What's it supposed to look like?

522
00:28:09,146 --> 00:28:10,717
- Like this.
- This?

523
00:28:10,717 --> 00:28:13,880
- This aloof?
- Right.

524
00:28:13,880 --> 00:28:15,402
When he's rapping,

525
00:28:15,402 --> 00:28:17,119
when he's dancing,

526
00:28:17,119 --> 00:28:19,640
he's both fierce and cool.

527
00:28:19,640 --> 00:28:21,119
Fierce and cool.

528
00:28:21,119 --> 00:28:23,599
Fierce, cool.

529
00:28:23,599 --> 00:28:26,248
- Fierce, cool.
- Fierce, cool.

530
00:28:26,248 --> 00:28:27,440
No.

531
00:28:27,440 --> 00:28:28,519
No?

532
00:28:28,519 --> 00:28:30,334
- Fierce.
